title: World Series: Phillies Hit 5 Homers in Game 3 Win Over Astros
description: In the first World Series game in Philadelphia since 2009, the Phillies took Houston’s Lance McCullers Jr. deep five times and cruised to victory.
dc:creator: David Waldstein
media:description: Bryce Harper’s two-run home run in the first inning set the tone as Philadelphia crushed Houston in Game 3 of the World Series on Tuesday.
